description: From in- +‎ lace. Compare Old English enlacen (“to entangle, involve”), Old French enlacier, French enlacer. See lace, and compare enlace.

verbs.description: inlace (third-person singular simple present inlaces, present participle inlacing, simple past and past participle inlaced)

entries.meaning: To work in, as lace; to embellish with work resembling lace.
examples: O let these armes inlace thee
